<subSubSection id="C370656FFFACFF99FF5B4C665538FC09" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BD536E4FFACFF99FF5B4C665538FC09" blockId="32.[151,1436,764,1221]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
TYPE LOCALITY. “Karman et Gedrosia” [= 
<collectingRegion id="49AEF806FFACFF99FD454C66549BFCF7" box="[649,739,836,859]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Kerman</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49AEF806FFACFF99FCD34C6655D2FCF1" box="[799,938,836,861]" country="Pakistan" name="Balochistan" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Baluchistan</collectingRegion>
]; restricted to Saidabad [Zeydabad], SW of 
<collectingRegion id="49AEF806FFACFF99FF5B4C4A5689FCD3" box="[151,241,872,895]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Kerman</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFACFF99FED24C4557CEFC2C" author="Smith, M. A." box="[286,438,871,896]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="ref65609" refString="Smith, M. A. (1935) The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Reptilia and Amphibia. Vol. II. Sauria. Taylor and Francis, Ltd., Red Lion Court, Fleet Street, London, 440 pp. [Reprint Edition 1974, Today and Tomorrow's Printers and Publishers]" type="book" year="1935">Smith (1935)</bibRefCitation>
, but later 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFACFF99FDE54C455497FC2C" author="Szczerbak, N. N." box="[553,751,871,896]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="ref66117" refString="Szczerbak, N. N. (1974) Palearctic lizards. Akademija Nauk Ukrainskoi S. S. R., Istitut Zoologii, Kiev, 296 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1974">Szczerbak (1974)</bibRefCitation>
designated a 
<typeStatus id="54D18846FFACFF99FC404C45558BFC2C" box="[908,1011,871,896]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">lectotype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingRegion id="49AEF806FFACFF99FBF64C4A52EFFCD3" box="[1082,1175,872,895]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Kerman</collectingRegion>
, although elsewhere in his paper (p. 245) he still gives Saidabad as the type locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C370656FFFACFF99FF5B4C925555FB0C" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="distribution">
