DISTRIBUTION. E 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFACFF99FE924C9257F6FC6B" box="[350,398,944,967]" name="Iran" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFACFF99FE554C8D545DFC64" box="[409,549,943,968]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFACFF99FDFC4C8D54EBFC64" box="[560,659,943,968]" name="Pakistan" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD536E4FFACFF99FF5B4CF655DCFBF4" blockId="32.[151,1436,764,1221]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<materialsCitation id="3B023CB9FFACFF99FF5B4CF655D9FBF4" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3342274381" collectionCode="NHMW" country="Iran" location="Vienna" municipality="All" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" specimenCode="NHMW 36761" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Esfahan">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7674FFACFF99FE914CF657EDFC47" box="[349,405,980,1003]" name="Iran" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation id="13512A61FFACFF99FE6F4CF6578DFC41" box="[419,501,980,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 92–97. 92" captionStartId="87.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-48@87.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="87" captionText="FIGURES 92–97. 92. Eremias fasciata. 93. Eremias grammica. 94. Eremias intermedia. 95. Eremias kavirensis. 96. Eremias kopetdaghica. 97. Eremias lalezharica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929750/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 92</figureCitation>
. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BB1AC9EFFACFF99FDCC4CF6545CFC41" box="[512,548,980,1005]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">All</collectingMunicipality>
provinces east of the 55° meridian and south of the Kopet Dagh. The record by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FFACFF99FF5B4CD557AAFBBC" author="Mozaffari, O. &amp; Parham, J. F." box="[151,466,1015,1040]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="569 - 573" refId="ref60069" refString="Mozaffari, O. &amp; Parham, J. F. (2007) A new species of racerunner lizard (Lacertidae: Eremias) from Iran. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 58, 569 - 573." type="journal article" year="2007">Mozaffari &amp; Parham (2007)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingRegion id="49AEF806FFACFF99FDDA4CD554CCFBA3" box="[534,692,1015,1040]" country="Iran" name="Esfahan" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Esfahan Prov.</collectingRegion>
and that in the 
<location id="8EB5603FFFACFF99FCAD4CD555CAFBBC" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C387F2FFACFF99FF5B4DDE550AFB69:8EB5603FFFACFF99FCAD4CD555CAFBBC" box="[865,946,1015,1040]" country="Iran" municipality="All" name="Vienna" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" stateProvince="Esfahan">Vienna</location>
museum (
<specimenCode id="DBCC9E9FFFACFF99FBEA4CD552ABFBBC" box="[1062,1235,1015,1040]" collectionCode="NHMW" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/91g3-0mnw" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="Museum">NHMW 36761</specimenCode>
) from Kashan are dubious. More plausibly they could be a misidentified 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FFACFF99FCC34B3F55D9FB99" authorityName="Darevsky &amp; Szczerbak" authorityYear="1978" box="[783,929,1052,1077]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="andersoni">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FFACFF99FCC34B3F55D9FB99" box="[783,929,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">E. andersoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distributed in the area and having the same dorsal colour pattern of alternating dark and light longitudinal stripes
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD536E4FFACFF99FF5B4B465555FB0C" blockId="32.[151,1436,764,1221]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
HABITAT. Sandy or gravelly plains or silty alluvia with scattered steppe shrubby vegetation (
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FFACFF99FB254B4653EDFBD1" box="[1257,1429,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FFACFF99FB254B465341FBD7" box="[1257,1337,1124,1147]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Acacia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FFACFF99FA864B4653EDFBD1" box="[1354,1429,1124,1149]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Alhagi" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Alhagi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FFACFF99FF5B4BAA577CFB33" box="[151,260,1160,1183]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FFACFF99FF5B4BAA577CFB33" box="[151,260,1160,1183]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Artemisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FFACFF99FEDE4BAA5709FB33" baseAuthorityName="Anderson" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[274,369,1160,1183]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tamaricaceae" genus="Tamarix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FFACFF99FEDE4BAA5709FB33" box="[274,369,1160,1183]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Tamarix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) under which these lizards seek refuge.
</paragraph>
